    unhide
  </span>
</span>
    </span>
</h2>
<section class="userbody">
    

    <div class="mapAndAttrs">
   <p class="attrgroup">
           <span>compensation: <b>$9.50 - $12.00, depending on experience</b></span><br>
           <span>employment type: <b>employee's choice</b></span><br>
   </p>
    </div>

    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://honolulu.craigslist.org/oah/fbh/6046941264.html"></div>
        </div>
We are looking for the same things every other food and retail establishment is, all the basics: show up on time, work hard when it's busy, busy yourself around the shop when it's not, customer and service focused personality, a commitment to serving an outstanding product, professional demeanor, love your mom but not too much, blah blah blah<br>
<br>
Really what makes a great scooper is a sense of fun and an ability to sell. You should be outgoing and like to talk with people. A LOT. Meeting new folks should energize you and make you happy, not make you want to hide in the back room. You should love the look of joy on a little kid's face when she's getting the ice cream she has been dreaming about all day. Ben &amp; Jerry's is a fun company, and we want to work with fun people.<br>
<br>
Some days it's crazy busy in the shop and you are exhausted when your shift is over. Other days we spend time cleaning up and making our space hospitable because it's pouring down rain outside and nobody wants ice cream. <br>
<br>
It's a big plus if you have a smartphone and can do email, but it's not required. You'll still need internet access though, because we do all our shift scheduling online.<br>
<br>
And then there's the sales aspect of the job.......... <br>
<br>
Does offering samples, talking about different flavors and ingredients, asking people if they'd like to try our newest thing, or even just chatting about our belief in Fair Trade and non-GMO ingredients make you feel icky and nasty inside? Are you right now re-considering your future selling for The Man and promoting the capitalistic oppression of The People? <br>
<br>
Hey, we get it. We're a weird, hippy-dippy ice cream company that makes money selling sugary frozen-milk products while passionately trying to make the world better. Plenty of moral contradictions! The world is a morally complex place and we respect your position, but please don't apply. <br>
<br>
A scooping job is also a sales job. If that makes you unhappy, we will be unhappy, customers will be unhappy, and working together WON'T BE FUN. IT WILL BE MISERABLE. <br>
<br>
If you drive a beater car with flames on the sides or a horn that plays mariachi music, you're probably hired. Will you wear a funny hat or wig to make customers smile? Even better. But if you're a high drama person that's a serious negative; you should go work for one of our competitors. We are happy to give you their numbers.<br>
<br>
If after reading all this and you are still into us, send us your resume! <br>
<br><br>
We are growing and looking for great people to join our teams.<br>
Hiring part time and full time positions at our Ward Village & Windward Mall locations.<br>
We are also looking for team members who are interested to be a part of our Events & Catering team and as well as an awesome Cake Decorator.<br>
<br><br>
We are currently hiring for our <b>Windward Mall &amp; Ward Village </b> locations.  <br>
<b>Windward Mall</b>, we are looking for a few week days (9:00am - 4:00pm).<br>
<b>Ward Village</b>, we are looking for week days (9:00am - 4:00pm), week nights (3:30pm - 10:30pm) and weekend shifts (9:00am - 4:00pm, 12:00pm - 6:00pm and  3:30pm - 12:00am).<br> 
If you have open flexibility, that would be ideal, but if you are only available specific days and times, we will consider that as well. <br>
<br>

If you are beholden to parental units (we love parents!), please make sure that they understand that if you are offered a position with us, you have a <b>commitment and responsibility</b> to work your assigned shifts.  That may mean working early, late or longer hours than what they may be comfortable with. If you're under 18, we would love to meet your parent(s) since they may be a part of our extended team.  <br>

<br>
We are looking for applicants that can make a <b>long term commitment of at least 6 months</b>.  If you CANNOT or WILL NOT be able abide by this commitment, please DO NOT APPLY.<br>
<br>
If you cannot wake up early, or you have a curfew to get home by, or don't have a reliable means of transportation OR if you prefer to watch TV, hang out with friends, SnapChat, Facebook and Tweet all day long - please DO NOT APPLY.
<br>
When applying, please let us know which location you are applying for and how many hours you are looking to work in a given week.<br><br>
<b>
We normally respond within 24 hours of receiving a resume.  If we don't hear from you within 48 hours of our email, we will assume that you've spilt the milk and are crying over it!  
<br></b>
<br>
Finally, if we call you for an interview, wear something that makes you laugh or makes you happy! We'd love to see your weird tattoo of peg-legged pirates drinking lattes. Or maybe you can kiss your ripped biceps as you brag about how perfect your arms are for scooping. <br>
<br>
Sure, we want to know you can work hard, but whatever you do, don't forget to bring your sense of FUN!    </section>

